content: We've made so many different initiatives or participated in so many different things over the last, let's call it 12 months to both enhance markets we're in today, take advantage of all the M&A disruption that's going on in the marketplace and bring on new talent, again, either to bolster existing markets or to take advantage of operating in new markets. Now again, they're not looking as great as they were a year ago where people were able to get lower rates and take out additional cash as there's a lot of pressure there in that part of the marketplace, which is why I think the entire multifamily market has just slowed down dramatically.
